  "texts": [
    "This works brilliantly when it comes to writing fluent English (or some other native language), because nearly all the contributors of views it is examining are fluent writers.",
    "It can even extract, using statistical tools, a selection representing one native language or another and translate between them, and it can select certain styles of writing located within one language and associate them with an author.",
    "But it fails when it comes to the substance because there is no well-organised substance.",
    "Even within human science, the hard job is to know how to pick the few papers that need to be studied from the snowstorm of publications and preprints that might initially seem worth of consideration.",
    "Then we move outwards to works that emerge from the fringe and alternative paradigms."
